<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-840-707  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 840 707.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Dec 6 1990 v35 n25 p220(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Programmable resistor shifts phase.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Raman, Ajoy; Radhakrishna, Rao.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The RC network commonly used for phase shifting sinusoidal signalscan be replaced with a digitally programmable circuit.andP;  Thecircuit illustrated in the article substitutes for the traditionalcircuit's resistor with a discrete, multiplying d-A converter(MDAC), functioning as a programmable resistor.andP;  The resultingcircuit is a frequency-independent, digitally programmable phaseshifter, achieving a phase-shifting range of 50 to 179 degrees.andO;The AD 7512 CMOS switches and resistors form a programmableresistor between circuit nodes A and B. The capacitor, along withthe digitally variable resistance, form an RC phase-shift network.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ProgrammableDigital SignalsResistorsNetworksIntegrated circuits.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   This digitally programmable phase shifter can replace a fixed RCnetwork. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>